fields.data: hello
... so important you are going to bed early...
black
... but you are worried nonetheless...
... that you will have that nightmare again...
And even if your feet bring you closer to the door...
... you always dread entering the tower...
... and not finding your way out again.

There's only one way for you...
... forward.
... and there is nothing else you can do but put your foot in front of the other...
... and when you think you're about to reach the end...
So you walk...
... and walk...
... and walk...
This one goes on and on...
... and on and on....

... and when you think you're at the end...
... another corridor awaits you...
... they are dreadfully long, aren't they...
... but there is not much else you can do...
Ah... finally the end of the corridor...

You can't go back...
... you can never go back...

... oh no...
... not that again...

Last time you saw this...
... it did not end well...

You'd do anything to get away from it...
... to not have to touch it again...
You still can't go back...

... you can't ever get away.
You can't change the dream...
... not matter how hard you try.
... but never through this one.
... only going in one direction.
... and you're not certain you'd like to get there.

Trinkets from another time.
Ones you thought you left behind...
...clearly you did not.

Remnants of another life.
Bits and pieces forgotten...
... yet they are still here.

You were certain you did not take them.
You "could not deal" then.
So why... why can't you forget it?

Why is it still haunting your dreams?
Why do they keep appearing when you tried your best to erase them?
Why? Why? why? WHY?
- The End -
